<img typeof="foaf:Image" src="images/Bioseminal.jpg" width="320" height="242" alt="BioSentinel Fluidics Card" >
BioSentinel’s microfluidics card, designed at NASA Ames, will be used to study the impact of interplanetary space radiation on yeast. Once in orbit, the growth and metabolic activity of the yeast will be measured using a 3-color LED detection system and a metabolic indicator dye. Here, pink wells contain actively growing yeast cells that have turned the metabolic dye from blue to pink color.<br>
